column5:
Single-cell transcriptomic profile of innate cell populations in mesenteric lymph nodes of inflammatory bowel disease patients
(Submitter supplied) Innate immune cells, including dendritic cells (DCs), monocytes (Mono), macrophages (Mac), natural killer (NK) and innate lymphoid cells (ILC), contribute to chronic inflammation in lymphoid tissues. Here, we characterized the innate immune cell landscape in inflamed mesenteric lymph nodes (MLNs) of patients with inflammatory bowel diseases (IBD) at the single-cell level. CITE-seq analysis unveiled the molecular signature of 11 Mono/Mac/DC (MMDC) and 7 NK/ILC enriched clusters in human MLNs. more...
